Dedicated Servers | Managed Dedicated Server Hosting - Hivelocity HostingSAVE UP TO 20% WHEN YOU PREPAY!Dedicated ServersHundreds of Dedicated Servers Deployed Every MonthLimited Time Offer: Save up to 50% with promotional pricing and prepayment discountsChat nowView All ServersCall NowHome/Products/Dedicated ServersDedicated Servers backed by our 24/7 on-premise support team.Private LAN for IPMI & Power ManagementService Monitoring with Email & Text AlertsCloud DNS Management InterfaceNetwork Layer Intrusion Detection SystemIPv6 Support10GB Cloud StorageFree Inbound Bandwidth99.99% Uptime SLAGPU capable24/7 Phone, Chat and Ticket Support (Hablamos Español)15 minute or less average response timeBoth Public & Private VLAN NetworksServer Hardening Upon DeploymentBandwidth ReportingIntelligently Routed Blend of 7 Transit ProvidersPeering with AWS, Microsoft, Google & MoreFree Private Traffic Between Multiple Servers & Data Centers—Private LAN for IPMI & Power Management
                Each server includes IPMI (ip management interface) access over our secure private network giving administrators enhanced access to the server beyond simple SSH or Remote Desktop.  View server health report from the IPMI control panel located within your myVelocity portal.
            Service Monitoring with Email & Text Alerts
                Setting up service monitoring is easy within the myVelocity control panel.  Monitor packet loss, ping times, HTTP, SMTP, FTP and IMAP services.  Receive text message or email alerts when services fail or fall out of norms.
            Cloud DNS Management Interface
                Easily manage all your domains with myVelocity’s hosted DNS manager.  Supports SOA, NS, A, AAAA, CNAME, MX, TXT, and SRV records.
            Network Layer Intrusion Detection System
                We protect our customers by constantly monitoring our network for signatures of malicious activity such as port scanning and brute force, DOS, TCP, UDP and ICMP based attacks.  Automated mitigation tactics are triggered once an attack is detected blocking the source IP from our network.  Optional enterprise grade DDoS protection plans with packet scrubbing are also available.
            IPv6 Support
                IPv6 is included and fully supported.
            10GB Cloud Storage
                Setup and manage your free cloud storage within the myVelocity portal.  Additional cloud storage can be added for just $.20 per GB.  Check out our knowledgebase for articles and videos detailing how to utilize this storage for backup of your server and server files.
            Free Inbound Bandwidth
                All of your inbound bandwidth is free and not measured against the transfer included with each server.
            99.99% Uptime SLA
                While we have a proven track record of 100% network and power uptime for years, we guarantee 99.99% and will compensate you with service credits if we ever fall short of that.
            24/7 Phone, Chat & Ticket Support(Hablamos Español)Our technical support team is located on-site at the data center that hosts your server and is available to assist you all day every day.  We can provide you with technical support in English or Spanish. Both Public & Private VLAN Networks
                All servers include a public VLAN for inbound and outbound traffic, in addition to a 1Gbps private VLAN network for intra-datacenter connections.  This private network is utilized when accessing data center services like cloud storage and daily backups.    These 2 networks are in addition to the out-of-band management network for IPMI access.
            Server Hardening Upon Deployment
                Upon server deployment we ensure your OS is hardened and updates are applied.
            Bandwidth Reporting
                Within the myVelocity portal customers are provided detailed bandwidth reports that show both inbound and outbound throughput.  Usage data can be graphed by the month, week, day or down to the hour.
            Intelligently Routed Blend of 7 Transit Providers
                The Hivelocity network consists of an intelligently routed blend of Level 3, TWTC, CenturyLink, NTT, Cogent, Seabone & XO transit.   We enhance our network performance with the use of specialized software (Noction) that adds a layer of intelligence to our routing.  In short, our intelligent routing protocol chooses the absolute fastest path available enabling us to reduce jitter and improve over 20,000 routes per day over standard BGP.  Our incredible global network performance is just one reason we have customers in over 130 countries.
            Peering with AWS, Microsoft, Google and More
                We further improve our already incredible network by establishing peering points of presence in strategic regions of the country and with specific organizations that our customers commonly interact with.  We currently have peering points established in Miami, Atlanta and Los Angeles enabling us to control network destinations and shorten hops once data hits those locations.  Additionally our network is directly peered with organizations like Amazon, Apple, Google, Microsoft, Charter, Cox Communications, Hurricane Electric and over 300 more similar entities allowing us to optimize network performance between our network and theirs.
            Free Private Traffic Between Multiple Servers & Data Centers
                Each Hivelocity server is outfitted with at least 3 network interfaces.  1.  Public network 2.  Private network.  3. IPMI access.  Our private network allows us to cross-connect multiple servers within the data center.  This service is provided free of charge.  Additionally, each of our data centers is connected with a point to point private network allowing servers across different facilities to communicate free of charge.
